contentrichtext.text: '''''CIRA''''' can refer to: *CIRA, [[COSPAR international reference atmosphere]], an empirical model of the upper [[atmosphere]] *CIRA, IRS - Common Interest Real estate Association - The IRS name for home owners associations, condominium associations, property owner associations, time-share associations. *[[Ä†ira]], popular Serb singer *[[Canadian Internet Registration Authority]] *[[Centre International de Recherches sur l'Anarchisme (CIRA)]] in Lausanne, Switzerland *Centro Italiano Ricerche Aerospaziali, the [[Italian Aerospace Research Centre]]. *[[CIRA-FM]] *[[Central Illinois Regional Airport]] *[[S. 2611|Comprehensive Immigration Reform Act]], Senate Proposed Legislation, S. 2611 *[[Continuity Irish Republican Army]] *[[Cooperative Institute for Research in the Atmosphere]] *[[Yale University Center for Interdisciplinary Research on AIDS (CIRA)]] *Cellular Internet Routing Appliance CIRA, a network device from Feeney Wireless [http://www.feeneywireless.com] *[[Client Initiated Remote Access]], a remote access technology from Intel *[[Certified Insolvency and Restructuring Advisor]], a qualification issued by the Association of Insolvency and Restructuring Advisors {{disambig}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Cira}} [[Category:Broadcast call sign disambiguation pages]]
